oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Concert: Fit For a Queen: Salute to Kitty Wells - 2009-05-09
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance by Laura Cantrell and her band honoring Kitty Wells from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on May 9, 2009. In support of a Kitty Wells exhibit. Includes interview segment with Laura Cantrell, Chris Scruggs and Paul Burch.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Laura Cantrell; Paul Burch; Chris Scruggs;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Performances include; Making Believe; I Don't Claim To Be An Angel; Don't Break The Heart; The Churches Off The Interstate; Trains And Boats And Planes; Can't Wait; Train Of Life; interview conducted by Mick Buck; Kitty Wells Dresses; Down South In New Orleans (Paul Burch); All The Same To You; Not The Trembling Kind; It Wasn't God Who Made Honky Tonk Angels; Old Downtown;
